afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model

Class DVD

  • java.lang.Object
    • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.Element
      • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.SimpleElement
        • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.DVD
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>

    public class DVD
extends SimpleElement
    Class whose instances represent a DVD. A DVD has a title and duration. Instances of DVD are ordered in ascending ordered of their duration.
    Author:
    (original) Daniel Gomes, Filipe Maia, Pedro Antunes, (revisionSOLID) Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Element dvd)
        Sorts instances of DVD by ascending ordered of their duration; if two instances of DVD have the same duration, they are lexicologically ordered by their title.

        If dvd is not an instance of DVD, it is returned the result of the compareTo of class Element.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Element>
        Overrides:
        compareTo in class Element
        Parameters:
        dvd - The instance of Element with which to compare to.
        Returns:
        A value less than 0 if this is less than element; 0 if this and element have the same title and the same runtime type or a value greater than 0 if this is greater than element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If element is null.
